text:
Hey, everyone.
Dewey Duck here.

And today, I'm counting down
some of my favorite quests
of all time.

First up at number four
is Scrooge's mission
to rescue Beakley.

This adventure pretty
much has it all.

The only thing that could
make it better is way more me.

There's like, zero
me in this one.

Up next in my top
quest countdown,

we're diving deep to number
three with an epic deep sea
adventure.
Dewey under the Seven Seas?

Sounds like 20,000
Leagues of awesome.
I'm a regular Jacques Dew-steau.
That's some diving guy.
Trust me, it's a great pun.

Up next in my top quest
list, coming in at number two

is a tale as old as
time, as in time travel.

Oh, and did I mention it
happens during Christmas?

So please consider this
adventure my gift to you, which
means you now owe me a present.

And now the moment you've
all been waiting for.

Number one on my top
quest count-Dew-n,

raiding the Doomsday Vault. With
an exciting adventure to an icy

vault and a whole
lot of times where

my mom is super proud
of me, this epic quest
easily takes number one.

Thanks for watching my
top adventures countdown.

And be sure to watch my
next countdown coming soon--

1,000 reasons why Dewey
is the best triplet.
Here's a sneak preview.

Number 1,000-- I'm
great at counting.
Number fo-- four-- three--
[stuttering] hold on.
I'll get it.
And, um--
